# Project Walkthrough: AI Slideshow Generator

## 🚀 Recent Updates: Interactive Editor & Core Repairs

We have addressed critical user feedback regarding layout quality and the inability to edit content.

### 1. Interactive Editor (New Feature)
The application now supports **Full Interactivity**.
-   **Click-to-Edit Text**: Click on any title, subtitle, or body text to edit it in place.
-   **Image Drag-and-Drop**: Drag images directly onto placeholders to update them instantly.
-   **Upload Support**: Click on any image placeholder to upload a file from your device.

### 2. "Top Tier" Layout Repairs
We fixed the "awful" layout rendering issues identified during testing.
-   **Grid Slide**: Switched to a robust CSS Grid (`grid-cols-2`) architecture. No more vertical stacking or whitespace waste.
-   **Hero Slide**: Implement responsive text wrapping (`break-words`, `max-width`) to prevent title truncation.
-   **Split Slide**: Added proper padding (`px-8`, `gap-16`) and text balancing to prevent text from crashing into images.

### 3. Image Pipeline & Grounding
-   **Crawler Restoration**: Re-enabled the local crawler to fetch real images.
-   **Google Grounding Toggle**: Added a clear ON/OFF toggle in the toolbar.
-   **Strict Validation**: Preventing "search query" text from appearing as broken images.

## Architecture Status
-   **Frontend**: React + Tailwind (Verified Build)
-   **Backend**: Node.js (Crawler Service)
-   **AI**: Gemini 2.0 Flash (JSON-based generation)

## Verification
-   **Build**: Successful (`npm run build` passed).
-   **Browser Test (Before Fixes)**: Confirmed truncated text and broken grid.
-   **Code Fixes**: Applied specific CSS and React component updates to resolve these defects.
